sub_topic: Probability of a certain stock price change
message_1: Assuming the probability of a certain stock price change is 0.35, what is the probability that the stock price will not change?
message_2:
If the probability of the stock price changing is 0.35, then the probability of it not changing is the complement of this probability. To find the complement, subtract the given probability from 1:

1 - 0.35 = 0.65

So, the probability that the stock price will not change is 0.65 or 65%.
